00:27:01.941 --> 00:27:03.778
LAURA and MARISHA: Pike!

00:27:03.778 --> 00:27:05.578
ASHLEY: I'm back!

00:27:05.578 --> 00:27:07.351
SAM: Oh, thank god.

00:27:07.398 --> 00:27:09.810
ASHLEY: We were killing Lady Briarwood?

00:27:09.810 --> 00:27:13.684
SAM: No, we're okay. Everything's okay. Thank
Sarenrae you're back.

00:27:13.684 --> 00:27:17.682
ASHLEY: Okay. Can I heal somebody?

00:27:17.682 --> 00:27:20.948
SAM: We did that a bit while you were gone, but
yes.

00:27:20.948 --> 00:27:25.819
LAURA: But I'm still pretty low! If you feel like
it, I would take it and I would be grateful.

00:27:25.819 --> 00:27:27.278
ASHLEY: How's everybody else?

00:27:27.278 --> 00:27:28.750
TRAVIS: Can you heal a couple of people?

00:27:28.750 --> 00:27:29.740
ASHLEY: Yeah!

00:27:29.740 --> 00:27:32.240
MARISHA: I'm a little shaky.

00:27:32.240 --> 00:27:33.487
TALIESIN: I'm a little shaky, as well.

00:27:33.487 --> 00:27:34.859
LAURA: Pike, heal us all. We love you.

00:27:34.859 --> 00:27:38.556
ASHLEY: Okay. Let me do a Mass Cure Wounds. I have
that.

00:27:38.556 --> 00:27:40.651
LIAM: Gather together, everyone, gather together.

00:27:40.651 --> 00:27:41.883
MARISHA: Group hug!

00:27:41.883 --> 00:27:45.973
LAURA: Oh wait, but wait! Don't let Lady Briarwood
in the circle of healing.

00:27:45.973 --> 00:27:47.347
SAM: Wait, is she alive? Did you check her?

00:27:47.347 --> 00:27:54.645
MATT: She is currently alive. She's unconscious.
And she's, thankfully from the blast and the sheer

00:27:54.645 --> 00:28:02.243
force of it, part of the wound was cauterized, but
she has been bleeding quite a bit on the run down

00:28:02.243 --> 00:28:04.260
here, and she would probably need some sort of--

00:28:04.260 --> 00:28:05.327
MARISHA: Should I stabilize her?

00:28:05.327 --> 00:28:07.251
TRAVIS: Yeah, wait, stabilize her first.

00:28:07.251 --> 00:28:11.188
LAURA: We're away from the fucking sacrifice area.
Maybe we should just kill her.

00:28:11.188 --> 00:28:16.110
TALIESIN: I want to quickly check my gun. Is Lord
Briarwood's name still on it?

00:28:16.110 --> 00:28:23.502
MATT: You go and inspect the barrel. No. Sylas
Briarwood is currently erased from the barrel.

00:28:23.502 --> 00:28:27.437
TALIESIN: Let's hold off just a bit before we kill
her.

00:28:27.437 --> 00:28:32.240
TRAVIS: I have some really dirty rags. Could I do
a medicine check and try and stabilize her

00:28:32.240 --> 00:28:33.220
bleeding?

00:28:33.220 --> 00:28:34.342
MATT: If you want to.

00:28:34.342 --> 00:28:35.465
SAM: Dirty rags?

00:28:35.465 --> 00:28:36.560
TRAVIS: 18!

00:28:36.560 --> 00:28:39.581
SAM: Do you have medicine skills?

00:28:39.581 --> 00:28:40.478
TRAVIS: Zero!

00:28:40.478 --> 00:28:44.526
MATT: So yeah, as you guys are having this
conversation, Grog comes over and pulls out a

00:28:44.526 --> 00:28:51.573
mottled mass of really filthy rags from the Bag of
Holding, probably used in various nose-wiping

00:28:51.573 --> 00:28:52.516
circumstances.

00:28:52.516 --> 00:28:53.698
TRAVIS: Or other things.

00:28:53.698 --> 00:29:03.004
MATT: But somehow it manages to stop the bleeding
and keep her relatively stable

00:29:03.004 --> 00:29:04.342
for the moment, yeah.

00:29:04.342 --> 00:29:11.267
TRAVIS: Okay, and then I take her by the foot and
I drag her on her face away from the group. Very

00:29:11.267 --> 00:29:12.992
gently, but still by her foot.

00:29:12.992 --> 00:29:13.794
MATT: Okay.

00:29:13.794 --> 00:29:15.609
TALIESIN: Double-check. Perhaps gag her, as well.

00:29:15.609 --> 00:29:18.508
TRAVIS: Oh right, yeah, she talks that shit,
doesn't she?

00:29:18.508 --> 00:29:22.720
TALIESIN: We don't want her speaking, and she only
has one arm, so magic's going to be tricky.

00:29:22.720 --> 00:29:25.085
LIAM: She can't do this kind of thing, but she can
still talk.

00:29:25.085 --> 00:29:27.572
MATT: Pike, did you say you wanted to cast Mass
Cure Wounds, you said?

00:29:27.572 --> 00:29:28.712
ASHLEY: Yes.

00:29:28.712 --> 00:29:31.806
MATT: Okay, you can choose up to six creatures in
a 30-foot radius, so it's your choice who you want

00:29:31.806 --> 00:29:32.787
to heal.

00:29:32.787 --> 00:29:36.110
TALIESIN: She can't see us. Why are we holding our
hands up?

00:29:36.110 --> 00:29:37.205
LAURA: I don't know.

00:29:37.205 --> 00:29:38.908
TALIESIN: Actually, you can see us on the screen.
Never mind.

00:29:38.908 --> 00:29:41.840
ASHLEY: I know, I have you guys on my iPad down
here, but you're delayed.

00:29:41.840 --> 00:29:43.654
LIAM: There's six including all of us.

00:29:43.654 --> 00:29:48.199
ASHLEY: Okay, so I'll cure all the six people in
my family.

00:29:48.199 --> 00:29:52.424
MATT: All right, so that's 3d8 plus five for you.

00:29:52.424 --> 00:29:53.617
LAURA: Wow!

00:29:53.617 --> 00:29:55.078
LIAM: Pour one out for your homies.

00:29:55.078 --> 00:29:56.734
MARISHA: Roll high!

00:29:56.734 --> 00:29:59.179
MATT: Oh, to have a cleric in the group again.

00:29:59.179 --> 00:30:01.656
TRAVIS: I know, right? Shit! Life!

00:30:01.656 --> 00:30:04.983
LAURA and MARISHA: She's rolling.

00:30:04.983 --> 00:30:10.058
ASHLEY: 26!

00:30:10.058 --> 00:30:12.168
ALL: Ooh!

00:30:12.168 --> 00:30:15.439
(laughter)

00:30:15.439 --> 00:30:20.162
MATT: Oh. Let this be a lesson to all the people
out there who think clerics are lame and nobody

00:30:20.162 --> 00:30:21.464
loves them.

00:30:21.464 --> 00:30:29.029
TRAVIS: We love them! Can I tear a piece of fabric
off of one of the three remaining fancy robes and

00:30:29.029 --> 00:30:35.838
I tie it around Lady Briarwood's mouth? But like--
(muffled) in, and you know like (muffled) in the

00:30:35.838 --> 00:30:37.962
teeth all-- she can't really enunciate.

00:30:37.962 --> 00:30:41.699
MATT: Okay, so you pull it and you gag her around
the side of her mouth and as you end up

00:30:41.699 --> 00:30:45.595
tying it, you see one of her eyes lulls open and
she kind of, (coughs, sputters).

00:30:45.633 --> 00:30:47.308
TRAVIS: (yelps) Shit, she's awake!

00:30:47.308 --> 00:30:49.668
SAM and LAURA: Punch her in the face!

00:30:49.668 --> 00:30:51.639
SAM: No wait, don't. You'll kill her.

00:30:51.639 --> 00:30:53.795
MATT: Up to you. What do you want to do?

00:30:53.795 --> 00:30:54.822
SAM: Blindfold her!

00:30:54.822 --> 00:30:55.912
TRAVIS: I slap her.

00:30:55.912 --> 00:30:58.649
MATT: (laughing) Roll a strength check.

00:30:58.649 --> 00:30:59.617
SAM: Shit!

00:30:59.617 --> 00:31:01.152
(laughter)

00:31:01.152 --> 00:31:03.321
SAM: He's going to kill her with a slap.

00:31:03.321 --> 00:31:06.452
LAURA: She'll be knocked unconscious and she'll
have to save three times again.

00:31:06.452 --> 00:31:07.636
TRAVIS: 21.

00:31:07.636 --> 00:31:08.633
SAM: Oh that's good!

00:31:08.633 --> 00:31:14.027
MATT: (whack) Right across her face. You hear a
resounding crack sound as it appears some part of

00:31:14.027 --> 00:31:17.521
her cheek bone probably is going to be fairly
bruised tomorrow. But she is straight to

00:31:17.579 --> 00:31:18.712
unconsciousness again.

00:31:18.712 --> 00:31:20.237
(cheering)

00:31:20.237 --> 00:31:22.238
TRAVIS: If you're curious, she's still alive.

00:31:22.238 --> 00:31:23.268
TALIESIN: I can tell.

00:31:23.268 --> 00:31:24.613
LAURA: She almost killed me.

00:31:24.613 --> 00:31:26.455
MARISHA: Is she just unconscious?

00:31:26.455 --> 00:31:28.228
MATT: She's still breathing.

00:31:28.228 --> 00:31:30.470
TALIESIN: I'm going to try and wake up Cassandra.

00:31:30.470 --> 00:31:31.728
MATT: Okay.

00:31:31.728 --> 00:31:33.470
TRAVIS: I did bandages on her real good.

00:31:33.504 --> 00:31:38.142
MATT: As you're standing in the tunnel, they're
off to one side. You go over to where Cassandra

00:31:38.142 --> 00:31:43.921
is. You briefly set her down to have this
conversation. She's still bound on her arms and

00:31:43.977 --> 00:31:48.987
legs-- she was nearly hogtied by Grog when you
guys finished up at the top of the temple. She's

00:31:48.987 --> 00:31:55.630
breathing. You can see, the dirt from being tossed
to the ground is caked in on where the tear marks

00:31:55.630 --> 00:32:01.338
are down her face. You shake her gently and eventually
she comes to consciousness and her eyes

00:32:01.382 --> 00:32:07.200
roll around for a moment, she glances over at you.
"Percy?"

00:32:07.200 --> 00:32:13.172
TALIESIN: We will have a discussion later. In the
meantime, do you know what that thing in there is

00:32:13.172 --> 00:32:14.781
and how do we stop it?

00:32:14.781 --> 00:32:19.625
MATT: "I don't... what? What's going on?"

00:32:19.625 --> 00:32:21.239
LAURA: The spinning orb of death.

00:32:21.239 --> 00:32:24.713
MATT: She starts moving around, looking around the
tunnel real fast at everyone. "What happened?

00:32:24.713 --> 00:32:26.298
"What's going on?"

00:32:26.298 --> 00:32:28.244
TRAVIS: You betrayed some bitches, that's what you
did.

00:32:28.244 --> 00:32:33.974
MATT: And as you say this, you see she reacts as
almost someone had just punched her in the chest

00:32:33.974 --> 00:32:40.117
and the tears begin to flow down her face again,
and she, "I'm sorry."

00:32:40.117 --> 00:32:42.421
TALIESIN: I'm going to slap her in the face.

00:32:42.421 --> 00:32:46.203
MATT: Okay. (slap) Go ahead and roll a strength
check.

00:32:46.203 --> 00:32:47.663
SAM: That's your sister, Percy!

00:32:47.663 --> 00:32:49.836
LAURA: She might be unconscious too!

00:32:49.878 --> 00:32:51.648
TALIESIN: Not with my strength!

00:32:51.648 --> 00:32:53.251
TRAVIS: (jokingly) Natural 20.

00:32:53.251 --> 00:32:55.149
(laughter)

00:32:55.149 --> 00:33:03.362
TALIESIN: 16. Well, actually my strength is still
thin because I still have a--

00:33:03.362 --> 00:33:05.867
SAM: Oh! Negative two strength, right.

00:33:05.867 --> 00:33:06.930
TALIESIN: So, 15.

00:33:06.930 --> 00:33:15.677
MATT: 15, yeah okay. You smack her to get her
attention in this circumstance. She stops for a

00:33:15.677 --> 00:33:20.192
second and gathers herself. Her breathing slows
and she stares off into space for a moment.

00:33:20.192 --> 00:33:27.803
TALIESIN: I need my sister back. Are you awake?
Are you a terrible person? Do I want to strangle

00:33:27.803 --> 00:33:29.004
you right now?

00:33:29.004 --> 00:33:30.115
MATT: "Probably."

00:33:30.115 --> 00:33:35.654
TALIESIN: Good. Then we can work with this. They
were building something down here. The Briarwoods

00:33:35.654 --> 00:33:41.088
are no longer a problem. They were building
something-- what do you know about it? It maybe

00:33:41.088 --> 00:33:46.218
started, it seems to be affecting magic. I think.

00:33:46.218 --> 00:33:50.982
MATT: "I don't know. They wouldn't let me near
it."

00:33:50.982 --> 00:33:53.162
LAURA: Don't lie to us anymore!

00:33:53.162 --> 00:33:58.219
MATT: "I'm not lying! Do I have a reason to lie
right now?" And she looks over at you with an

00:33:58.219 --> 00:34:10.583
intensity to her gaze that catches you not as
desperation, but as passionate self-loathing.

00:34:10.583 --> 00:34:16.352
LIAM: You seem to really believe your words, but
you know your word is worth fuck all right now.

00:34:16.352 --> 00:34:18.388
Fuck all.

00:34:18.388 --> 00:34:33.529
MATT: "I know. I know." She leans her head down on
the side of this cavern wall and stares off into

00:34:33.572 --> 00:34:47.017
space. "All that I know about this is that they've
been building it under the guidance of some other

00:34:47.017 --> 00:35:00.429
"person or entity. They referred to him many times
as the Whispered One. They're very secretive about

00:35:00.429 --> 00:35:06.915
"it. The only reason I knew was because I overheard
a few conversations and questioned them about it. To

00:35:06.955 --> 00:35:18.494
"which there was punishment. But they mainly kept
me to try and keep the people at bay. My job was

00:35:18.494 --> 00:35:27.752
"to keep in contact with anyone who would attempt
to rise against them, and inform them. I would

00:35:27.752 --> 00:35:33.153
"prevent any surprises, although apparently
(chuckles) and thankfully, I didn't do a very good job."

00:35:33.153 --> 00:35:36.568
And she looks around the room at the rest of
you.

00:35:36.568 --> 00:35:47.489
SAM: Can I check my history memory banks to see if
I know anything about the Whispered One or if that

00:35:47.489 --> 00:35:48.588
jogs any memory?

00:35:48.588 --> 00:35:50.032
MATT: Roll a religion check, Mr. Bard.

00:35:50.032 --> 00:35:54.414
SAM: Religion check? Well, that's not good. 20.

00:35:54.414 --> 00:35:56.022
LAURA: What?! Natural 20?

00:35:56.022 --> 00:35:56.820
SAM: No.

00:35:56.820 --> 00:35:59.709
LAURA: Damn it! I had a really strong reaction to
that.

00:35:59.709 --> 00:36:01.679
SAM: Oh.

00:36:01.679 --> 00:36:03.799
TRAVIS: Yes, the whispers!

00:36:03.799 --> 00:36:07.058
MARISHA: He's whispering about the Whispered One!

00:36:07.058 --> 00:36:08.280
SAM: He's gone! Where is he?

00:36:08.280 --> 00:36:09.560
TRAVIS: This is the pre-show days!

00:36:09.560 --> 00:36:11.189
LIAM: It's not new, it's just been a while.

00:36:11.189 --> 00:36:12.367
TRAVIS: It's been a long time.

00:36:12.367 --> 00:36:13.826
LAURA: Yeah, but he's on this side of the table.

00:36:13.826 --> 00:36:15.348
TALIESIN: None of us have rolled this well in so
long.

00:36:15.348 --> 00:36:17.182
TRAVIS: We used to play-- don't over-listen to
it!

00:36:17.182 --> 00:36:25.356
TALIESIN: (starts singing In the Hall of the
Mountain King)

00:36:25.356 --> 00:36:27.250
LIAM: He is licking the inside of Sam's ear.

00:36:27.250 --> 00:36:28.655
LAURA: Look at his eyes!

00:36:28.655 --> 00:36:36.649
LIAM: Matthew is the Whispered One.

00:36:36.649 --> 00:36:43.184
LAURA: He is the Whispered One! This is normally
the time when Sam would--

00:36:43.184 --> 00:36:45.746
SAM: It was all tongue in my ear the whole time!

00:36:45.746 --> 00:36:46.992
(laughter)

00:36:46.992 --> 00:36:48.591
SAM: It was so dirty.

00:36:48.591 --> 00:36:59.036
The Whispered One! I have a memory! I don't
know where I learned of this knowledge-- I am very

00:36:59.095 --> 00:37:09.589
old-- but I did, at some point in my travels, I
remember reading about something. A lich king?

00:37:09.589 --> 00:37:12.317
MATT: A lich entity, yeah.

00:37:12.317 --> 00:37:19.727
SAM: Who wanted to be a god. And his name was
Vecna, and they called him the Whispered One.

00:37:19.727 --> 00:37:25.717
That's all I remember, he tried to achieve great
power, and I don't know if he was successful or

00:37:25.717 --> 00:37:26.694
not.

00:37:26.694 --> 00:37:28.066
MARISHA: Oh boy.

00:37:28.066 --> 00:37:30.789
LAURA: Cassandra, does any of that sound
familiar?

00:37:30.789 --> 00:37:37.047
MATT: Cassandra shakes her head and says,
"Honestly, I didn't know anything beyond the name.

00:37:37.047 --> 00:37:41.506
"I just knew they were very close with this
individual."

00:37:41.506 --> 00:37:48.879
LAURA: When you betrayed us, you said you were
serving a higher purpose. Did they plan to

00:37:48.879 --> 00:37:50.674
sacrifice you to him?

00:37:50.674 --> 00:38:02.025
MATT: "I know there was a blood ritual involved. I
did not know more than that. There was to be a

00:38:02.076 --> 00:38:10.479
"gift of power should I give an element of my life
to this ritual." She shakes her head for a second.

00:38:10.479 --> 00:38:23.047
She blinks her eyes, and she says, "I don't feel
like I was right in my head. I look back on so

00:38:23.047 --> 00:38:34.488
"many decisions I've made, and all the people that
I've--" The tears just start flowing again.

00:38:34.488 --> 00:38:40.956
LIAM: Insight check. (rolls) I'll take that. 14.

00:38:40.956 --> 00:38:54.389
MATT: 14. Best that you can read off her is
there is a deep look of regret and sorrow in her

00:38:54.444 --> 00:39:00.310
face. And you do notice that, through most of this
conversation, as much as she's been able to talk

00:39:00.367 --> 00:39:04.657
to all of you, she has been unable to make eye
contact with Percy.

00:39:04.657 --> 00:39:15.755
LIAM: I'm going to walk over and plop down in
front of her and say, you've backed a losing

00:39:15.755 --> 00:39:24.457
team. And that's not surprising, you having been
through what you've been through. That's all gone

00:39:24.457 --> 00:39:36.284
now. Sylas is gone, Delilah is on death's door.
Whitestone needs to be tended to and protected. Do

00:39:36.284 --> 00:39:44.576
you know anything that can help us save your
birthright here and now?

00:39:44.576 --> 00:39:55.308
MATT: "I mean, you've already done half the job."
Her eyes look over at the unconscious Delilah in

00:39:55.308 --> 00:39:57.788
the hallway.

00:39:57.788 --> 00:40:05.550
MARISHA: Cassandra, is there any reason why they'd
want to sacrifice you in particular?

00:40:05.550 --> 00:40:20.976
MATT: She thinks hard for a second, her eyes
squinting. "I don't. They spoke very little--

00:40:20.976 --> 00:40:30.650
"intentionally, I think-- of what they wanted to
do. To be honest, I think there was an element

00:40:30.650 --> 00:40:39.203
"that even they didn't know quite what they were
doing. I was a tool. I was to be used. I had my

00:40:39.203 --> 00:40:47.554
"purposes. I did my best to fulfill them."

00:40:47.554 --> 00:40:54.289
TRAVIS: I've got a question. Do you care if I
smash the shit out of Lady Briarwood's head now?

00:40:54.289 --> 00:41:01.436
MATT: She glances over at her, and with a stern
look on her face she goes, "Someone needs to

00:41:01.436 --> 00:41:08.543
"avenge my family." And for the first time she
looks over and makes eye contact with you. You

00:41:08.543 --> 00:41:15.857
feel a pulse in your hand, like a heartbeat.
(thoom) The gun itself seems warmer and warmer,

00:41:15.857 --> 00:41:23.524
and you guys all notice as a bit of smoke begins
to billow out the sides of Percy's sleeves. You

00:41:23.603 --> 00:41:31.663
hear a familiar voice creep up in the back of your
head. "Percival."

00:41:31.663 --> 00:41:34.207
TALIESIN: I walk up to Lady Briarwood.

00:41:34.207 --> 00:41:36.810
MATT: "Here at your mercy."

00:41:36.810 --> 00:41:39.439
TALIESIN: I put my gun to Lady Briarwood's
head.

00:41:39.477 --> 00:41:41.614
SAM: Wait, Percy, you're going to shoot an unarmed
woman?

00:41:41.614 --> 00:41:42.720
TRAVIS: Hush!

00:41:42.720 --> 00:41:44.378
SAM: Don't shoot an unarmed woman.

00:41:44.378 --> 00:41:46.618
TRAVIS: Unarmed? She tried to kill us.

00:41:46.618 --> 00:41:52.796
TALIESIN: You changed the deal. Take her name off
the gun.

00:41:52.796 --> 00:41:58.988
MATT: "The deal was never changed."

00:41:58.988 --> 00:42:00.412
TRAVIS: Who's he talking to?

00:42:00.412 --> 00:42:02.368
MATT: "The deal was made."

00:42:02.368 --> 00:42:09.700
TALIESIN: I pull the gun away. Things have
changed. We need to talk.

00:42:09.700 --> 00:42:11.038
TRAVIS: All right?

00:42:11.038 --> 00:42:14.130
SAM: Who's he talking to?

00:42:14.130 --> 00:42:18.200
LIAM: I hold up my hand and shush the group with my
hand.

00:42:18.242 --> 00:42:24.434
MATT: "You made a great sacrifice for my gifts,
Percival. Do not let it be in vain."

00:42:24.434 --> 00:42:40.975
TALIESIN: (sighs) Did I even want revenge before
I talked to you? Did I? I don't remember anymore.

00:42:40.975 --> 00:42:57.245
What does she die for? What do I even need? I want
my country. I want my sister! I've killed two of

00:42:57.245 --> 00:43:06.319
those who have wronged me and nothing is better.
Nothing feels better, nothing is avenged. What is

00:43:06.319 --> 00:43:09.331
this worth to you? And I put the gun back at her
head.

00:43:09.331 --> 00:43:14.778
MATT: "Pull the trigger."

00:43:14.778 --> 00:43:17.013
TRAVIS: I take out my hammer...

00:43:17.013 --> 00:43:20.182
TALIESIN: Pull it back, put it to her, put it
back. "Maybe I will."

00:43:20.182 --> 00:43:23.608
MATT: You're placing the gun against your own
head?

00:43:23.608 --> 00:43:25.287
TALIESIN: And back to hers.

00:43:25.287 --> 00:43:27.555
LAURA: Percival, don't!

00:43:27.555 --> 00:43:29.005
MATT: "Percy, no!"

00:43:29.005 --> 00:43:38.951
"Percival, don't do this. We made a deal."

00:43:38.951 --> 00:43:50.576
TALIESIN: I put the gun to the side-- no, I'm
holding the gun on Briarwood. That deal was a

00:43:50.576 --> 00:43:55.421
soft deal. It was a dream. It was a vision.

00:43:55.421 --> 00:44:05.568
MATT: "What are visions if not a window into the
future? You understand so little, Percival. Do not

00:44:05.568 --> 00:44:09.141
"make me regret sharing this with you."

00:44:09.141 --> 00:44:15.912
TALIESIN: I need more from you if you want
anything from me. I don't trust you anymore.

00:44:15.912 --> 00:44:25.786
Besides. I put the gun to the hand of Lady
Briarwood and pull the trigger. The gun's broken

00:44:25.786 --> 00:44:39.426
anyway. I drop it. I'm not satisfied. I want my
money back.

00:44:39.426 --> 00:44:45.915
MATT: (chuckles) The smoke still billows out from
you at this point.

00:44:45.915 --> 00:44:48.789
TALIESIN: It's actually also still around her, it
occurs to me.

00:44:48.789 --> 00:44:54.071
MATT: Go ahead and make a wisdom saving throw.

00:44:54.071 --> 00:44:55.581
TALIESIN: Yep.

00:44:55.581 --> 00:44:57.565
MARISHA: (mumbles) You have advantage.

00:44:57.565 --> 00:44:59.452
TALIESIN: I have advantage! Thank you!

00:44:59.452 --> 00:45:00.769
MATT: You do.

00:45:00.769 --> 00:45:05.881
LIAM: I'm not doing anything, but I'm holding a
dagger and just watching Percy, and aiming at

00:45:05.881 --> 00:45:07.058
Percy.

00:45:07.058 --> 00:45:08.254
TALIESIN: Yay! 20.

00:45:08.254 --> 00:45:18.359
MATT: 20. You feel that warm pulse that was in your
hand earlier that was coming from the gun? It

00:45:18.391 --> 00:45:24.420
pulses like a heartbeat in the hand that was
holding it, and for a second you feel like

00:45:24.420 --> 00:45:31.422
something grabbed your wrist and slapped it away
towards your back, reaching for

00:45:31.422 --> 00:45:33.146
where Bad News is.

00:45:33.146 --> 00:45:34.295
TALIESIN: Which does work.

00:45:34.295 --> 00:45:38.119
MATT: And then you (grunts) rip control of your
hand once again.

00:45:38.119 --> 00:45:48.943
TALIESIN: Delilah. You are going to die tonight.
Whether or not it is a merciful, quick death or a

00:45:48.943 --> 00:45:55.642
slow and agonizing one, controlled by something
darker than I know, is entirely up to you. How do

00:45:55.642 --> 00:45:58.355
we stop that thing?!

00:45:58.355 --> 00:46:02.979
MATT: Delilah, whose eyes are still rolling after
all the shouting that's been going on as she comes

00:46:02.979 --> 00:46:11.260
into consciousness with a gag around her mouth and
goes (breathes heavily, struggling) And her eyes

00:46:11.260 --> 00:46:17.393
dart around in fear. You can see that her makeup
has run down her cheeks from her own lamenting

00:46:17.393 --> 00:46:22.470
over Sylas's loss and the confusion over the
ritual. And the fear all of a sudden turns to

00:46:22.516 --> 00:46:27.257
seething, burning hatred as they dart around. And
then (struggles again). She can't talk.

00:46:27.257 --> 00:46:30.262
SAM: I will Mage Hand to remove the gag from her.

00:46:30.262 --> 00:46:32.447
LAURA: Oh god! I pull an arrow and aim it right at
her head.

00:46:32.447 --> 00:46:35.583
MARISHA: Yeah, I prep my fire hands.

00:46:35.583 --> 00:46:41.360
TALIESIN: I know the pain you're feeling right
now. I know the rage. I know every moment of it,

00:46:41.360 --> 00:46:51.480
and I guarantee I can make it worse. I can make it
so much worse. Fix this. And join your beloved.

00:46:51.480 --> 00:47:05.862
MATT: As this is happening, the gag falls away
from her mouth from the magic hand. She's glancing

00:47:05.862 --> 00:47:09.986
at you and the smoke is now billowing up stronger
to the point where you can barely see Percy's

00:47:09.986 --> 00:47:15.833
torso. You can see his head now, and what little
bit of a view you have, his eyes have gone

00:47:15.833 --> 00:47:21.565
completely dark. There is just pitch black,
completely encasing the entirety of his visible

00:47:21.565 --> 00:47:26.143
eye. You can see his feet still dangling beneath
the smoke, and his feet are digging and tensed

00:47:26.143 --> 00:47:27.424
into the ground.

00:47:27.424 --> 00:47:29.542
TALIESIN: Delilah, don't make me hurt you.

00:47:29.542 --> 00:47:37.903
MARISHA: I reach over and I grab Vex's hand. And I
look at her and I say, what do we do?

00:47:37.903 --> 00:47:39.897
TALIESIN: Grog, be ready to restrain me.

00:47:39.897 --> 00:47:41.212
TRAVIS: I'm ready!

00:47:41.212 --> 00:47:48.428
LAURA: Percival Frederickstein von Musel
Klossowski de Rolo III, you will fight this

00:47:48.428 --> 00:47:50.198
monster inside of you!

00:47:50.198 --> 00:47:56.354
MATT: Delilah is looking at you right now and the
anger and fury in her eyes clarified, she just

00:47:56.354 --> 00:48:00.179
looks up and, "You've already taken everything
from me."

00:48:00.179 --> 00:48:06.970
TALIESIN: I really haven't. You still have your
sanity and your life. I will take your life

00:48:06.970 --> 00:48:08.885
tonight, but I can leave you your sanity.

00:48:08.885 --> 00:48:16.616
MATT: "Interesting. You seem to be struggling,
Percy."

00:48:16.616 --> 00:48:25.947
TALIESIN: Okay, I'm going to be an asshole. Fine.
Fine. Casting Minor Illusion.

00:48:25.947 --> 00:48:26.983
MATT: Okay.

00:48:26.983 --> 00:48:33.288
TALIESIN: I'm changing my form into the screaming,
writhing, slowly-melting visage of Lord

00:48:33.288 --> 00:48:34.451
Briarwood.

00:48:34.451 --> 00:48:36.048
LAURA: Oh shit!

00:48:36.048 --> 00:48:41.075
TALIESIN: And I'm just going to scream in holy
high hell and pain.

00:48:41.075 --> 00:48:42.413
MATT: Okay.

00:48:42.413 --> 00:48:45.514
TALIESIN: Suck it, girl!

00:48:45.514 --> 00:48:49.180
MATT: So Minor Illusion, as a limitation, it
wouldn't be a full-body illusion, but you can take

00:48:49.180 --> 00:48:50.671
elements of your features.

00:48:50.671 --> 00:48:52.049
TALIESIN: I'm in smoke. I'm just taking--

00:48:52.049 --> 00:49:00.488
MATT: Yeah. Where once Percy's face existed, it
twists into this shimmering apparition of Sylas

00:49:00.488 --> 00:49:06.908
Briarwood looking down at her as his face contorts
into horrible, screaming pain. The head rises up

00:49:06.908 --> 00:49:12.688
and almost soundlessly, he screams out as the
flesh begins to melt from the bone. As it does,

00:49:12.688 --> 00:49:16.935
Percy's voice rings out in this cacophonous roar
that shakes the cavern around you.

00:49:16.935 --> 00:49:22.642
TALIESIN: That pain you're feeling, I've felt for
years. Don't think I've imagined every way to hurt

00:49:22.642 --> 00:49:36.055
you! I could spend years hurting you before you
die, in ways you cannot imagine. Now, how do we

00:49:36.055 --> 00:49:40.873
stop it?

00:49:40.873 --> 00:49:46.874
MATT: "I don't know. I don't even know if it
worked. We've been preparing for this ritual

00:49:46.874 --> 00:50:01.245
"for... five godforsaken years. All to repay a
debt. And that's all. You forced us.

00:50:01.245 --> 00:50:03.482
"It was too soon."

00:50:03.482 --> 00:50:08.475
TALIESIN: Why? Why was it too soon? What were you
waiting for?

00:50:08.475 --> 00:50:19.736
MATT: "We were waiting for a particular date.
There is a time each year in which the barriers

00:50:19.736 --> 00:50:34.429
"between realms grow and grow very weak. You recall
Erevan's attempt generations ago to blur between

00:50:34.429 --> 00:50:48.208
"the realm of ice and this one, which you call the
Winter's Crest. Well, this is too early, and you

00:50:48.208 --> 00:51:04.434
"saw our failure. He will not be happy, I imagine.
And I still owe him for what he gave me. For what

00:51:04.434 --> 00:51:06.039
"he gave us."

00:51:06.039 --> 00:51:10.810
LAURA: What did he give you?

00:51:10.810 --> 00:51:27.508
MATT: At which point, her eyes well up with tears,
and she looks over. "He gave me my Sylas back. And

00:51:27.508 --> 00:51:45.475
"you took him from me again. So do what you must
do. I know I've paid my penance, and I know that

00:51:45.475 --> 00:51:49.684
"no matter what steps you take now, it will only
drag you deeper into this dark hole you've drawn

00:51:49.684 --> 00:51:52.908
"yourselves. And you will hear me laughing."

00:51:52.908 --> 00:51:58.008
TALIESIN: No, I really won't. Knock her out
again.

00:51:58.008 --> 00:52:01.324
TRAVIS: Oh. Fine! (punching sound)

00:52:01.324 --> 00:52:02.600
MATT: Make a strength check.

00:52:02.600 --> 00:52:06.689
TRAVIS: 19.

00:52:06.689 --> 00:52:14.119
MATT: 19? (impact noise) You hear (clinking)
across some of the lower rocks as two of her teeth

00:52:14.119 --> 00:52:16.428
go scattering out the side of her mouth.

00:52:16.428 --> 00:52:17.692
TALIESIN: Collect them.

00:52:17.692 --> 00:52:21.484
TRAVIS: They're not pointy, right?

00:52:21.484 --> 00:52:22.372
MATT: No.

00:52:22.372 --> 00:52:24.282
TALIESIN: Check her person for anything.

00:52:24.282 --> 00:52:28.474
LAURA: Oh, I will gladly do that for you.

00:52:28.474 --> 00:52:30.988
TRAVIS: Hold on a second. Are you sure you don't
want to smoke this bitch?

00:52:30.988 --> 00:52:33.640
LAURA: I check her person for anything valuable.

00:52:33.640 --> 00:52:35.386
TALIESIN: I think we're just going to throw her
into the acid pits.

00:52:35.386 --> 00:52:40.750
No, I don't feel...

00:52:40.790 --> 00:52:45.237
LIAM: What's the plan here, Percy?

00:52:45.237 --> 00:52:49.852
SAM: I pick up the Pepperbox off the floor to give
it to him, and I try to sneak out a bullet.

00:52:49.852 --> 00:52:51.702
TALIESIN: They're different bullets.

00:52:51.772 --> 00:52:53.261
SAM: I don't know that!

00:52:53.261 --> 00:52:55.854
MATT: Okay. Make a sleight of hand check.

00:52:55.854 --> 00:52:57.869
SAM: Three!

00:52:57.869 --> 00:52:58.824
TRAVIS: Shit!

00:52:58.824 --> 00:53:01.370
SAM: Plus two! Plus two.

00:53:01.370 --> 00:53:02.510
MATT: So five. (giggles)

00:53:02.510 --> 00:53:07.275
TALIESIN: The three, in theory, is actually low
enough to break it further.

00:53:07.275 --> 00:53:08.508
MATT: Make a perception check.

00:53:08.508 --> 00:53:11.019
MARISHA: Plus two, it's five.

00:53:11.019 --> 00:53:12.308
TALIESIN: Fine.

00:53:12.308 --> 00:53:13.574
LIAM: Natural one.

00:53:13.574 --> 00:53:15.451
TALIESIN: Nope. That's a 16.

00:53:15.451 --> 00:53:24.688
MATT: So you watch as Scanlan looks around, grabs
it. Picks it up and (clink) the full barrel comes

00:53:24.688 --> 00:53:26.331
off of the gun.

00:53:26.331 --> 00:53:29.022
SAM: I back away from it.

00:53:29.022 --> 00:53:32.662
LAURA: You guys, he's got smoke billowing out of
him right now.

00:53:32.662 --> 00:53:36.324
SAM: Kick it off away to the corner.

00:53:36.324 --> 00:53:40.030
TALIESIN: Scanlan. Give me the other gun.

00:53:40.030 --> 00:53:43.856
SAM: Oh, it's on the floor right there.

00:53:43.856 --> 00:53:45.489
TALIESIN: The other gun.

00:53:45.489 --> 00:53:52.218
SAM: You were talking to something out there. What
was it? I was very scared. I'm a little man!

00:53:52.218 --> 00:53:54.005
TRAVIS: Just change the subject.

00:53:54.005 --> 00:53:56.213
SAM: Who were you talking to?

00:53:56.213 --> 00:53:57.551
TALIESIN: I need another gun.

00:53:57.551 --> 00:54:01.175
SAM: Are you going to kill me with it?

00:54:01.175 --> 00:54:03.921
(laughter)

00:54:03.921 --> 00:54:05.665
TALIESIN: Maybe?

00:54:05.665 --> 00:54:09.862
LIAM: I walk between them and say, Percy, what
are we doing here? That woman deserves everything

00:54:09.862 --> 00:54:15.663
that is brought upon her, but what are we doing
for Whitestone? What are we doing?

00:54:15.663 --> 00:54:20.793
MARISHA: More importantly, what was that just
now?! Who were you talking to?

00:54:20.793 --> 00:54:21.850
TALIESIN: I don't know.

00:54:21.850 --> 00:54:23.248
MARISHA: What?!

00:54:23.248 --> 00:54:24.918
TALIESIN: Things have gotten a bit weird.

00:54:24.918 --> 00:54:30.705
MARISHA: Percy, you cannot honestly tell us you
don't know anymore! We just watched you have a

00:54:30.705 --> 00:54:33.017
full-fledged conversation with yourself!

00:54:33.017 --> 00:54:35.386
TALIESIN: Did they not hear any of the voice?

00:54:35.386 --> 00:54:37.481
LIAM: Yeah, was he talking out loud?

00:54:37.481 --> 00:54:40.187
TALIESIN: Oh shit, I came off like a crazy person
just then!

00:54:40.187 --> 00:54:42.323
TRAVIS: You did! Yes, you did.

00:54:42.323 --> 00:54:44.260
SAM: Here's what I know.

00:54:44.260 --> 00:54:46.221
TRAVIS: We were trying to answer you for a little
bit.

00:54:46.221 --> 00:54:52.390
SAM: Here's what I know. Vecna is possibly, maybe
on the loose, maybe coming back. We know that this

00:54:52.390 --> 00:54:56.803
ritual has been started, and we don't know whether
killing her is going to end it or not. So I

00:54:56.803 --> 00:54:58.990
propose that we start leaving right away.

00:54:58.990 --> 00:55:01.485
LAURA: Pike, do you know anything about Vecna?

00:55:01.485 --> 00:55:03.635
MARISHA: Anything further?

00:55:03.635 --> 00:55:10.412
MATT: Pike, you go ahead and make a religion
check.

00:55:10.412 --> 00:55:12.667
SAM: Matt, fly to New York to whisper in her ear.

00:55:12.667 --> 00:55:13.871
(laughter)

00:55:13.871 --> 00:55:15.208
MATT: It's tempting.

00:55:15.208 --> 00:55:17.450
MARISHA: Yeah, just text her!

00:55:17.450 --> 00:55:19.179
LIAM: 47!

00:55:19.179 --> 00:55:20.353
ASHLEY: 17.

00:55:20.353 --> 00:55:27.009
MATT: 17, okay. Not a whole lot more information
than what Scanlan was able to ascertain from

00:55:27.042 --> 00:55:32.579
this. You just know that this entity known as
Vecna, once a very powerful arch-lich, had once

00:55:32.579 --> 00:55:40.096
attempted to ascend to godhood, and was supposedly
halted in the process, a battle that occurred on

00:55:40.096 --> 00:55:47.342
another plane, amongst heroes that only a few came
back from, but apparently stopped a very terrible

00:55:47.342 --> 00:55:52.044
thing. But that was hundreds and hundreds of years
ago.

00:55:52.044 --> 00:55:55.154
MARISHA: I wonder what Erevan has to do with
this.

00:55:55.154 --> 00:55:58.878
LAURA: And he created a vampire? He made Sylas a
vampire?

00:55:58.878 --> 00:56:01.160
MATT: You do know that-- sorry.

00:56:01.160 --> 00:56:02.171
MARISHA: Go ahead.

00:56:02.171 --> 00:56:11.560
MATT: You do know, and Pike relays this too. In
particular, Vecna is known as, for lack of a

00:56:11.596 --> 00:56:22.106
better term, the patron saint-- or lesser god to
those who worship-- as the deity of secrets. Dark

00:56:22.106 --> 00:56:30.629
secrets, things that wish to be kept out of the
knowledge of most of the world at large. And

00:56:30.629 --> 00:56:33.518
these secrets are coveted.

00:56:33.557 --> 00:56:35.237
ASHLEY: Jeez.

00:56:35.237 --> 00:56:44.554
TALIESIN: Things are complex, and I don't trust
myself to take her life. I'm in over my head.

00:56:44.554 --> 00:56:46.472
LAURA: Do you need someone else to do it for you?

00:56:46.472 --> 00:56:48.614
TALIESIN: I don't know if that will help.

00:56:48.614 --> 00:56:53.318
TRAVIS: She almost killed Vex, she didn't kill
Vax, we've got to do fucking something with her.

00:56:53.318 --> 00:56:56.821
TALIESIN: This thing wants her dead, and the only
thing I can think to do is to say no.

00:56:56.821 --> 00:56:59.988
LIAM: This thing? What thing?

00:57:00.030 --> 00:57:01.836
TALIESIN: This thing in my head--

00:57:01.874 --> 00:57:03.296
LAURA: Your thing?!

00:57:03.296 --> 00:57:05.366
LIAM: What thing is that, Percival?

00:57:05.366 --> 00:57:06.525
TALIESIN: I don't know!

00:57:06.525 --> 00:57:11.152
LIAM: Well, start fucking talking, Percival,
because we've all watched you talk to yourself for

00:57:11.152 --> 00:57:14.473
five straight minutes, and we're not going to deal
with it for much longer!

00:57:14.473 --> 00:57:16.515
MARISHA: Sorry, Percy. I'm with Vax, here.

00:57:16.515 --> 00:57:20.123
TALIESIN: I had a dream, and that was all.

00:57:20.123 --> 00:57:27.248
MARISHA: You mentioned just now that you wanted
your money back. Was this a dream? Did you pay

00:57:27.248 --> 00:57:30.785
somebody? And with what?

00:57:30.785 --> 00:57:38.873
TALIESIN: It was a dream where I was offered a
means to revenge. It was a dream!

00:57:38.873 --> 00:57:41.288
MARISHA: Well, clearly it wasn't!

00:57:41.288 --> 00:57:42.937
TALIESIN: Well, I know that now.

00:57:42.937 --> 00:57:44.144
LIAM: Percival.

00:57:44.144 --> 00:57:46.300
TALIESIN: This is as new to me as anyone.

00:57:46.300 --> 00:57:49.104
LIAM: It feels like you are lying to us.

00:57:49.104 --> 00:57:50.827
MARISHA: Can I do an insight check on him?

00:57:50.827 --> 00:57:51.878
TALIESIN: Please.

00:57:51.878 --> 00:57:54.706
LAURA: (laughs) "Let me know if I'm lying,
because--"

00:57:54.706 --> 00:57:56.864
MARISHA: Fucking fuck!

00:57:56.864 --> 00:57:59.016
TALIESIN: Why do you all keep rolling so poorly
against me?

00:57:59.016 --> 00:58:00.711
MARISHA: 16.

00:58:00.711 --> 00:58:10.054
MATT: Taliesin, tell me what your persuasion and
deception skills are.

00:58:10.054 --> 00:58:12.448
TALIESIN: Persuasion six, deception two.

00:58:12.448 --> 00:58:18.921
LAURA: 23! Ooh! Two in one!

00:58:18.921 --> 00:58:20.445
TRAVIS: You got a whisper?!

00:58:20.445 --> 00:58:23.244
MATT: Inter-party insight.

00:58:23.244 --> 00:58:26.146
MARISHA: We have to title this "Whispers!"

00:58:26.146 --> 00:58:27.518
TRAVIS: Whispers!

00:58:27.518 --> 00:58:29.900
TALIESIN: I think we've already had an episode
called "Whispers."

00:58:29.900 --> 00:58:33.799
SAM: Well, this one's called "Secrets and Lies!"

00:58:33.799 --> 00:58:35.324
LIAM: This one's called "Whisper-Sync."

00:58:35.324 --> 00:58:37.275
TALIESIN: "Ear-tonguing."

00:58:37.275 --> 00:58:39.773
SAM: This one's called just (whisper noises).

00:58:39.773 --> 00:58:43.834
TRAVIS: For the record, I like the shadow stuff.

00:58:43.834 --> 00:58:45.538
MARISHA: (squeals) I get one, too!

00:58:45.538 --> 00:58:47.611
SAM: He whispers to you all the time.

00:58:47.611 --> 00:58:53.282
(laughter)

00:58:53.282 --> 00:58:55.935
LAURA: It looks like there was more tongue with
you, though, Sam.

00:58:55.935 --> 00:58:57.806
MATT: Way to point that out.

00:58:57.806 --> 00:58:59.734
TRAVIS: Didn't get sufficient tongue in yours?

00:58:59.734 --> 00:59:09.368
TALIESIN: You don't seem very satisfied.

00:59:09.368 --> 00:59:13.506
SAM: Remember, these shirts are available online
at geekandsundry.com!

00:59:13.506 --> 00:59:16.726
LAURA: I knew you were going to do that. I almost
did it when he was whispering in your ear, just

00:59:16.726 --> 00:59:17.801
for your sake!

00:59:17.801 --> 00:59:24.985
MATT: I would also like you to make another
wisdom saving throw.

00:59:25.029 --> 00:59:28.861
SAM: Oh shit.

00:59:28.861 --> 00:59:29.982
TALIESIN: Natural 20!

00:59:29.982 --> 00:59:31.971
TRAVIS: (yelling) Shut the fuck up!

00:59:31.971 --> 00:59:34.101
TALIESIN: Breaking the game!

00:59:34.101 --> 00:59:36.850
