01:27:02.074 --> 01:27:03.044
LAURA: Whoa.

01:27:03.044 --> 01:27:05.332
MARISHA: And he's in that Faerie Fire, right?

01:27:05.332 --> 01:27:06.947
MATT: He is, currently, yeah.

01:27:06.947 --> 01:27:08.395
MARISHA: So you get advantage, yo.

01:27:08.395 --> 01:27:11.577
MATT: He didn't see it being cast. He withdrew
before it happened, so he steps right into it.

01:27:11.577 --> 01:27:15.667
TALIESIN: All right, starting with Bad News with a
sharpshooter.

01:27:15.667 --> 01:27:19.127
LAURA: We get advantage on attacking him?

01:27:19.127 --> 01:27:21.161
MATT: Yeah, all of your attacks on him currently
have advantage.

01:27:21.161 --> 01:27:29.616
TALIESIN: Thank god, because I rolled a one. 14?

01:27:29.616 --> 01:27:34.487
MATT: 14 unfortunately misses. You fire and
(ricochet noise) it seems that, in a strange way,

01:27:34.487 --> 01:27:38.355
the gentle pink dust is actually obscuring your
vision with the dark shadow in that vicinity and

01:27:38.355 --> 01:27:40.635
it blasts a piece of rock off the side of the
wall.

01:27:40.635 --> 01:27:42.105
TALIESIN: Firing again.

01:27:42.105 --> 01:27:43.281
MATT: So fire, reload.

01:27:43.281 --> 01:27:49.065
TALIESIN: Better! 26.

01:27:49.065 --> 01:27:52.242
MATT: 26 does hit. Go ahead and roll damage.

01:27:52.242 --> 01:28:14.988
TALIESIN: That's... That's pizza! I'm looking for
my dice. I didn't think this through. 25 points of

01:28:14.988 --> 01:28:16.095
damage.

01:28:16.095 --> 01:28:20.828
MATT: All right, good to know. This is piercing,
right?

01:28:20.828 --> 01:28:21.876
TALIESIN: Yeah.

01:28:21.876 --> 01:28:29.016
MATT: All right. The blast hits, but it appears
that the expected impact from the blast of Bad

01:28:29.016 --> 01:28:35.791
News-- a bit of smoke dissipates its impact and it
seems to not be as damaging as you expected it to

01:28:35.791 --> 01:28:40.828
be. All right, that brings us to the next person
who was holding their action. I believe Scanlan,

01:28:40.828 --> 01:28:43.462
you were? What do you want to do?

01:28:43.462 --> 01:28:53.219
SAM: There's precious little I can do, so I will
viciously mock it.

01:28:53.219 --> 01:28:55.440
(laughter)

01:28:55.440 --> 01:28:56.556
MATT: Good.

01:28:56.556 --> 01:29:03.705
SAM: Through the Hand Cone, I will say, don't you
know smoking is the number one cause of cancer and

01:29:03.705 --> 01:29:11.284
emphysema and will shorten your life by an
estimated ten to 20 years? It's not cool, and you

01:29:11.284 --> 01:29:12.836
shouldn't do it.

01:29:12.836 --> 01:29:14.247
TALIESIN: Is that all true?

01:29:14.247 --> 01:29:15.546
SAM: I'm BS-ing!

01:29:15.546 --> 01:29:16.627
TALIESIN: Oh, okay.

01:29:16.627 --> 01:29:24.856
MATT: Okay. It does not make its saving throw; it
rolled a four, so it takes 3d4 psychic damage. Go

01:29:24.856 --> 01:29:28.684
ahead and roll that. And it has disadvantage on
its next attack roll.

01:29:28.684 --> 01:29:31.121
LIAM: That fiend has low self-esteem.

01:29:31.121 --> 01:29:32.712
SAM: Five points.

01:29:32.712 --> 01:29:35.317
MATT: Five points of damage, boom.

01:29:35.317 --> 01:29:36.762
SAM: And it has disadvantage on what?

01:29:36.762 --> 01:29:43.188
MATT: On its next attack roll. Its eyes go darker
purple for a second, like it can't contemplate the

01:29:43.188 --> 01:29:49.815
fact that it just got insulted mid-battle, and
then they flare up again, even more furious. As

01:29:49.815 --> 01:29:51.302
part of that, it's going to use its reaction.

01:29:51.302 --> 01:29:53.164
SAM: Oh shit. Okay.

01:29:53.164 --> 01:29:57.810
MATT: It turns towards you and in-- what languages
do you speak?

01:29:57.810 --> 01:30:00.944
SAM: Gnome, Common. That's it.

01:30:00.944 --> 01:30:02.827
(laughter)

01:30:02.827 --> 01:30:08.755
MATT: You hear a muttering through your ears.
(mutters in foreign language) And for a second,

01:30:08.804 --> 01:30:12.586
you feel your field of vision close down like it's
focused entirely on you. You're currently marked

01:30:12.586 --> 01:30:15.079
by its Mark of Vengeance.

01:30:15.079 --> 01:30:16.784
SAM: Marked?

01:30:16.784 --> 01:30:21.871
MATT: Yeah. So, essentially, there's an effect
that's intent on you at the moment.

01:30:21.871 --> 01:30:23.318
SAM: Is it a charm effect?

01:30:23.318 --> 01:30:24.138
MATT: Nope.

01:30:24.138 --> 01:30:25.131
SAM: Damn it.

01:30:25.131 --> 01:30:27.458
MATT: All right, that ends your held actions.

01:30:27.458 --> 01:30:28.478
SAM: Is it a fear effect?

01:30:28.478 --> 01:30:29.309
MATT: No.

01:30:29.309 --> 01:30:30.170
SAM: Damn it!

01:30:30.170 --> 01:30:30.953
MATT: You're up.

01:30:30.953 --> 01:30:33.454
LIAM: Yeah, I just saw him mutter in Scanlan's ear
as I take both of my blades and I'm just going to

01:30:33.454 --> 01:30:37.880
slash both of them across and he's surrounded, so
this is a sneak attack, as well.

01:30:37.880 --> 01:30:38.745
MATT: Yes.

01:30:38.745 --> 01:30:40.846
LIAM: With advantage. The first one...

01:30:40.846 --> 01:30:42.694
LIAM and LAURA: (groan)

01:30:42.694 --> 01:30:47.990
LIAM: Is 16. Oh no! And the second one is a 27.

01:30:47.990 --> 01:30:49.280
MATT: Second one hits.

01:30:49.280 --> 01:30:50.408
LIAM: All right.

01:30:50.408 --> 01:30:54.266
MATT: You go to strike the first time, and as you
swing outward, you catch smoke and it dissipates

01:30:54.266 --> 01:30:56.972
around the blade and you stab into the side of the
wall.

01:30:56.972 --> 01:30:57.939
LIAM: Okay.

01:30:57.939 --> 01:30:59.263
MATT: Second attack (impact noise).

01:30:59.263 --> 01:31:05.311
LIAM: Here comes that sneak attack damage. That's
four plus six is ten plus... sneak attack,

01:31:05.311 --> 01:31:11.908
motherfucker! Ten, 16, 21, 22, 26, 28, 29 total.

01:31:11.908 --> 01:31:13.096
LAURA: That was 38.

01:31:13.096 --> 01:31:14.213
LIAM: Huh?

01:31:14.213 --> 01:31:15.352
LAURA: Just kidding.

01:31:15.352 --> 01:31:16.726
LIAM and LAURA: 29 total.

01:31:16.726 --> 01:31:18.502
LAURA: (singing) My math is awesome!

01:31:18.502 --> 01:31:24.572
MATT: Okay. This blade, however: as you stab into
this cloud of smoke, you feel there is more

01:31:24.572 --> 01:31:31.382
physical presence to where it was and it sinks in
and you feel this reverberation as it reacts to

01:31:31.382 --> 01:31:34.902
the pain. This dull (hoarse growl) growl sound.

01:31:34.902 --> 01:31:37.325
LIAM: I shout, hands off the gnome! as I do it.

01:31:37.325 --> 01:31:38.483
MATT: Okay.

01:31:38.483 --> 01:31:41.125
SAM: On my roll, do I still get a bonus?

01:31:41.125 --> 01:31:47.161
MATT: You used it last turn. That was his reaction
to you holding your action.

01:31:47.161 --> 01:31:50.642
SAM: No, but do I get my bonus action as part of
my move, or no?

01:31:50.642 --> 01:31:54.409
MATT: That would have had to be during your turn.
When you hold your action, you just get the action

01:31:54.409 --> 01:31:55.415
when it triggers.

01:31:55.415 --> 01:31:56.447
SAM: Got it.

01:31:56.447 --> 01:32:00.760
MATT: All right, so that ends Vax. Do you want to
do anything else?

01:32:00.760 --> 01:32:14.857
LIAM: No. Oh, I'm right up against it? I'm going
to use disengage and back up further back by my

01:32:14.857 --> 01:32:17.630
sister. Is that Vex and Keyleth?

01:32:17.630 --> 01:32:18.732
MATT: Right there, yeah.

01:32:18.732 --> 01:32:20.339
LIAM: I'm going to move between my two favorite
ladies.

01:32:20.339 --> 01:32:25.860
MATT: All right, there you go. Good to know. And
you were holding your action?

01:32:25.860 --> 01:32:26.996
LAURA: Yes.

01:32:26.996 --> 01:32:28.118
MATT: And you were holding your action.

01:32:28.118 --> 01:32:28.877
TRAVIS: Yeah.

01:32:28.877 --> 01:32:30.005
MATT: So everyone make your attacks.

01:32:30.005 --> 01:32:32.030
LAURA: Yes. Here's my question.

01:32:32.030 --> 01:32:32.979
MATT: Yes?

01:32:32.979 --> 01:32:39.393
LAURA: Because I want to be honest and I don't
remember if I said I dipped arrows in the second

01:32:39.393 --> 01:32:43.330
holy oil flask or if I put them on Trinket's
claws. Do we remember?

01:32:43.330 --> 01:32:44.720
MATT: You did all arrows.

01:32:44.720 --> 01:32:48.276
LAURA: That's fine. Then I'm going to shoot two
more holy arrows at him.

01:32:48.276 --> 01:32:52.265
Okay, well, I'll roll for that.

01:32:52.265 --> 01:32:55.055
MARISHA: With advantage!

01:32:55.055 --> 01:33:04.443
LAURA: With advantage, which is good. I'm going to
switch things. New ones. (gasps) What just

01:33:04.443 --> 01:33:05.414
happened?

01:33:05.414 --> 01:33:10.409
LIAM: Well, one of those was a 14, so that hit.
There's 14 and eight. 14 plus your attack. The

01:33:10.409 --> 01:33:12.143
second roll, she got a one and a two, so.

01:33:12.143 --> 01:33:19.629
LAURA: Seriously?! So one was a 25. And then 17.

01:33:19.629 --> 01:33:20.906
MATT: 17 misses, unfortunately.

01:33:20.906 --> 01:33:22.657
LAURA: I mean 19. 19 and a 25.

01:33:22.657 --> 01:33:24.821
MATT: What's the 19 from?

01:33:24.821 --> 01:33:27.297
LAURA: Was the first roll. And the second--

01:33:27.297 --> 01:33:28.756
MATT: Right, so you rolled a one and a two?

01:33:28.756 --> 01:33:31.608
LIAM: No, that was the second roll. The first was
an eight and a 14, plus her modifiers.

01:33:31.608 --> 01:33:36.973
LAURA: Oh. See, I was rolling-- I understand. I
was rolling it in my head differently, but we'll

01:33:36.973 --> 01:33:42.087
count it as that. I was counting it as that was my
first attempts at my first two attacks and my

01:33:42.087 --> 01:33:43.975
second attempts at my first two attacks.

01:33:43.975 --> 01:33:45.120
MATT: Yeah, it doesn't work that way.

01:33:45.120 --> 01:33:47.213
LAURA: Yeah, okay, that's fine. So, 25.

01:33:47.213 --> 01:33:50.182
MATT: Okay, so one of them hit. All right, so you
go ahead and roll damage on that.

01:33:50.182 --> 01:33:59.801
LAURA: I won't roll like that anymore. Where am I?
That's radiant damage and that's that. Here we go.

01:33:59.801 --> 01:34:01.044
All right.

01:34:01.044 --> 01:34:06.130
LIAM: Oh jeez, we've got a smoke demon, don'tcha
know?

01:34:06.130 --> 01:34:11.511
LAURA: 17 plus five is--

01:34:11.511 --> 01:34:12.346
LIAM: 24.

01:34:12.346 --> 01:34:13.316
LAURA: 24 points.

01:34:13.316 --> 01:34:17.933
MATT: 24 points of damage. So one of them flies
forward and misses--

01:34:17.933 --> 01:34:18.971
LAURA: 22.

01:34:18.971 --> 01:34:23.271
MATT: Yeah. Nearly grazes the top of your head,
just vanishing. You don't notice because you're

01:34:23.271 --> 01:34:28.073
currently (growls) right in his face. Second one
manages to strike it and splinter inside of its

01:34:28.073 --> 01:34:34.806
torso, and you can see a flash of energy from the
impact and it (squawking groan, growl) surveys the

01:34:34.806 --> 01:34:38.457
area around it. The smoke around it gets even more
intense, and you can see it flaring up.

01:34:38.457 --> 01:34:40.134
LAURA: I'm still against the wall, glowing.

01:34:40.134 --> 01:34:43.403
MATT: Yeah, so the smoke gets even thicker and
obscures it even further.

01:34:43.403 --> 01:34:50.895
LAURA: We should probably light up this area as
much as possible, FYI.

01:34:50.895 --> 01:34:52.251
MATT: And Grog?

01:34:52.251 --> 01:34:56.609
TRAVIS: I'm going to light it up with my flaming
war hammer. I turn and I swing at it.

01:34:56.609 --> 01:34:57.435
MATT: Okay.

01:34:57.435 --> 01:35:00.252
MARISHA: So metal.

01:35:00.252 --> 01:35:04.589
TRAVIS: Hey, that's good. 28?

01:35:04.589 --> 01:35:07.147
MATT: 28 hits. Second attack.

01:35:07.147 --> 01:35:08.955
TRAVIS: 26.

01:35:08.955 --> 01:35:10.512
MATT: 26 hits.

01:35:10.512 --> 01:35:13.315
TRAVIS: Nice. Oh, is it still covered in the holy
oil?

01:35:13.315 --> 01:35:17.527
MATT: Yes, so an extra 1d4 radiant damage on each
strike.

01:35:17.527 --> 01:35:24.393
TRAVIS: 21 for the first one.

01:35:24.393 --> 01:35:25.587
MATT: Okay.

01:35:25.587 --> 01:35:28.078
TRAVIS: With the radiant, fiery damage.

01:35:28.078 --> 01:35:31.884
MATT: Burning, holy wrath.

01:35:31.884 --> 01:35:35.891
TRAVIS: Fuck yes! 19, 20, 21. 22!

01:35:35.891 --> 01:35:42.995
MATT: 22. All righty. (impact sounds) Both hammer
blows strike it, battering the smoke around, and

01:35:42.995 --> 01:35:47.980
you can see as this hammer swings through its
body, the smoke almost swallows the light and for

01:35:47.980 --> 01:35:53.652
a second, it's almost like this dull orb of
darkness beneath the surface of a deep lake. And

01:35:53.699 --> 01:35:56.616
then as the hammer emerges from its body, the
light flares up again. It's almost like it's

01:35:56.616 --> 01:36:02.130
swallowing the light as you strike it. But it
seems to be taking the impacts pretty hard. All

01:36:02.130 --> 01:36:06.214
right, that ends your turn. Now, Orthax can take
his turn.

01:36:06.214 --> 01:36:07.068
LAURA: Oh no.

01:36:07.068 --> 01:36:09.511
MATT: All right, so let's see.

01:36:09.511 --> 01:36:10.996
ASHLEY: Wait, do I get my--

01:36:10.996 --> 01:36:14.301
MATT: That's right, you were holding, too. Yeah,
you can do it, too. Thank you for reminding me.

01:36:14.301 --> 01:36:15.443
LAURA: Yay, Pike!

01:36:15.443 --> 01:36:17.683
ASHLEY: Okay, I'm going to Guiding Bolt it.

01:36:17.683 --> 01:36:18.855
MATT: All right, go for it.

01:36:18.855 --> 01:36:22.036
LIAM: Your punishment will be more severe.

01:36:22.036 --> 01:36:24.570
(laughter)

01:36:24.570 --> 01:36:27.217
ASHLEY: All right, so 4d6--

01:36:27.217 --> 01:36:29.970
MATT: What level of Guiding Bolt are you doing?

01:36:29.970 --> 01:36:32.020
ASHLEY: Say one more time?

01:36:32.020 --> 01:36:33.778
MATT: What level of Guiding Bolt are you casting?

01:36:33.778 --> 01:36:40.322
ASHLEY: I'm going to do it at 4th because I have a
couple of 4th-level left.

01:36:40.322 --> 01:36:47.540
MATT: Okay, so that will be... (chuckles) Roll to
attack first. You have advantage on the attack

01:36:47.540 --> 01:36:51.222
roll because it's currently inside Faerie Fire, so
take the higher of the two rolls.

01:36:51.222 --> 01:36:56.204
LIAM: I would just like to say that Pike is very
eerie, yet beautiful in this iridescent glow of

01:36:56.204 --> 01:37:00.185
astral projection. It's hard to hear her
sometimes, but god damn it,

01:37:00.185 --> 01:37:01.663
she makes it look good.

01:37:01.663 --> 01:37:05.593
ASHLEY: Oh. Oh my god. I rolled a one and a
natural 20.

01:37:05.593 --> 01:37:07.808
(cheering)

01:37:07.808 --> 01:37:11.602
ASHLEY: What?

01:37:11.602 --> 01:37:19.930
MATT: Okay. So at 4th level, that would be 7d6
radiant damage.

01:37:19.930 --> 01:37:21.556
LAURA and MARISHA: Whoa!

01:37:21.556 --> 01:37:23.518
MARISHA: Wait, what did you cast?

01:37:23.518 --> 01:37:25.077
LAURA and TRAVIS: Guiding Bolt.

01:37:25.077 --> 01:37:26.389
MARISHA: Oh, fuck yeah!

01:37:26.389 --> 01:37:30.765
TALIESIN: 7d6?

01:37:30.765 --> 01:37:31.819
MATT: Yeah.

01:37:31.819 --> 01:37:33.037
SAM: That's a lot of d6.

01:37:33.037 --> 01:37:34.500
TALIESIN: Times two?

01:37:34.500 --> 01:37:36.262
LAURA: Is it times two after that because it's a
crit?

01:37:36.262 --> 01:37:40.552
MARISHA: It's a crit? Oh, right, because that's--
well, it's straight dice rolls. Or does she roll

01:37:40.552 --> 01:37:44.418
dice twice?

01:37:44.418 --> 01:37:49.279
MATT: For the purpose of ease, I usually double.
I'm just confirming one thing real fast.

01:37:49.279 --> 01:37:52.555
LIAM: She has just blinded us all in holy light is
what I'm assuming.

01:37:52.555 --> 01:37:54.205
MATT: Yeah, so go ahead and do your math.

01:37:54.205 --> 01:37:55.494
MARISHA: Little holy nuke.

01:37:55.494 --> 01:37:57.261
SAM: That's my Pike.

01:37:57.261 --> 01:37:58.657
ASHLEY: Okay.

01:37:58.657 --> 01:38:01.513
LAURA: What was it, Pike?

01:38:01.513 --> 01:38:03.074
ASHLEY: 21.

01:38:03.074 --> 01:38:04.297
LAURA: 21.

01:38:04.297 --> 01:38:06.149
MATT: 21. All right.

01:38:06.149 --> 01:38:09.267
LAURA: Times two?

01:38:09.267 --> 01:38:12.668
MARISHA: Times two, right?

01:38:12.668 --> 01:38:13.680
LAURA: Please?

01:38:13.680 --> 01:38:16.608
MATT: Yep, so that would be times two. Just
confirming. It has been a while since we've had

01:38:16.608 --> 01:38:21.798
any sort of spell-based crit. So that would be 42
points of radiant damage.

01:38:21.798 --> 01:38:23.329
LAURA, ASHLEY, and MARISHA: Whoa!

01:38:23.329 --> 01:38:28.281
MATT: As you release this bolt of energy out of
your hand, you see it charges up and fills up your

01:38:28.281 --> 01:38:33.448
hand, shaking, as you're waiting for the moment
where it might be too much to control, and your

01:38:33.448 --> 01:38:45.359
holy symbol flares as it releases and streaks
forward, right behind you. You were technically in

01:38:45.359 --> 01:38:51.538
melee with it, which would have given you
disadvantage on the attack, but you had advantage

01:38:51.538 --> 01:38:55.419
on him because of that and... we'll say it's fine.
It stays there because there were a lot of things

01:38:55.419 --> 01:38:59.118
giving advantage against him and then
disadvantage. We'll stay with it. As you turn

01:38:59.118 --> 01:39:02.714
around, you release it. Point blank, it slams into
the front and you can see where the smoke was

01:39:02.714 --> 01:39:06.719
swelling around it, it almost seems to be
scattered away from the impact of this radiant

01:39:06.719 --> 01:39:12.023
bolt, and for a second, this image of this
obscured, shadowy humanoid becomes very clear and

01:39:12.023 --> 01:39:18.076
you can see this extremely muscular humanoid torso
with elongated, exaggerated arms and fingers.

01:39:18.076 --> 01:39:26.317
Seemingly featureless across its body other than
its black, obsidian torso. No legs. They disappear

01:39:26.317 --> 01:39:33.290
into the smoke beneath it. Its head has the long,
hooked, birdlike skull beak, and where the eyes

01:39:33.290 --> 01:39:39.840
are, it's just this smooth, almost leathery
texture across the dark body itself. You can see

01:39:39.840 --> 01:39:45.550
what looks like faint horns that curve around the
back, that curl upward. And as it takes the

01:39:45.550 --> 01:39:51.701
impact, its head rolls back and you can hear this
billowing scream: (moaning cry) As it leans back

01:39:51.701 --> 01:39:57.274
forward towards you, it looks like it's having a
rough moment. Now we get to its turn.

01:39:57.274 --> 01:39:58.240
LAURA: Oh no.

01:39:58.240 --> 01:40:02.014
MATT: All right.

01:40:02.014 --> 01:40:08.750
TRAVIS: It farts a little cloud of smoke.

01:40:08.750 --> 01:40:11.531
TALIESIN: A lot of us are outside the Faerie
Fire.

01:40:11.531 --> 01:40:18.395
MATT: Based on that, it zeroes down on the little
ball of radiant energy staring before it that just

01:40:18.395 --> 01:40:24.468
blasted a hole in its form. It's going to take all
three of its strikes at you, Pike.

01:40:24.468 --> 01:40:26.777
TALIESIN: It's got disadvantage on its attacks.

01:40:26.777 --> 01:40:31.701
MATT: And has advantage because she's in Faerie
Fire, so it cancels it to a natural attack. That

01:40:31.701 --> 01:40:38.441
is 21. What's your AC?

01:40:38.441 --> 01:40:40.481
ASHLEY: 20.

01:40:40.481 --> 01:40:46.529
MATT: 20, so that hits. 27. And a natural one.

01:40:46.529 --> 01:40:47.930
MARISHA: Oh!

01:40:47.930 --> 01:40:49.943
